The paper deals with the joint design of precoding and backhaul compression strategies for cloud radio access networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and architecture (cs.AR). The paper discusses the optimization problem of maximizing the weighted sum-rate subject to power and backhaul capacity constraints, which is a typical problem in information theory and networking. The proposed algorithm is iterative, which is a common approach in control and systems engineering. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for multivariate compression, which is related to multimedia and architecture. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.AR.
